                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14624935" author="agarcia" created="Mon, 13 Jul 2015 16:55:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch that fixes the issue. The Apache HttpClient packages have been marked as &quot;optional&quot;, for the people that do not need the HTTP transport.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14630396" author="roger.meier" created="Thu, 16 Jul 2015 21:50:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14630458" author="hudson" created="Thu, 16 Jul 2015 22:31:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Thrift #1615 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift/1615/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Thrift/1615/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3242&quot; title=&quot;OSGi Import-Package directive is missing the Apache HTTP packages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3242&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3242&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; OSGi Import-Package directive is missing the Apache HTTP packages (r.meier: rev ecc2a6b60fd8fb29a56f700fd9667a71cade21b8)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lib/java/build.xml&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15830203" author="jking3" created="Thu, 19 Jan 2017 16:26:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could someone take a look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SM-3224&quot; title=&quot;Create OSGi bundle for libthrift-0.10.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SM-3224&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SM-3224&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and make sure the dependency list we are using in our build has everything I uncovered?&lt;br/&gt;
Also, do we even need a ServiceMix bundle for thrift 0.10.0 if the jar produced by a thrift build is OSGI compatible?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
